<li id="cite_note-31"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31" title="">^</a></b> For instance, "after the consecration of the bread and of the wine, there no longer remaineth the substance of the bread and of the wine, but the Body Itself and the Blood of the Lord, under the species and form of bread and wine; that is to say, under the accidents of the bread" (<a href="http://catholicity.elcore.net/ConfessionOfDositheus.html" class="external text" title="http://catholicity.elcore.net/ConfessionOfDositheus.html" rel="nofollow">Chapter VI of <i>Acts and Decrees of the Synod of Jerusalem</i></a>).</li>
